<p>
 <italic>Hydnora</italic> consists of eight species, namely, 
 <italic>H. visseri</italic> Bolin, E. Maass, and Musselman [
 <xref rid="B4-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">4</xref>,
 <xref rid="B5-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">5</xref>], 
 <italic>H. arabica</italic> [
 <xref rid="B1-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">1</xref>], 
 <italic>H. abyssinica</italic> A.Br. [
 <xref rid="B6-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">6</xref>,
 <xref rid="B7-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">7</xref>], 
 <italic>H. esculenta</italic> Jum. and H. Perrier [
 <xref rid="B4-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">4</xref>,
 <xref rid="B7-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">7</xref>], 
 <italic>H. africana</italic> Thunb. [
 <xref rid="B8-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">8</xref>], 
 <italic>H. triceps</italic> Dr√®ge and E. Mey [
 <xref rid="B9-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">9</xref>], 
 <italic>H. sinandevu</italic> Beentje and Q. Luke [
 <xref rid="B10-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">10</xref>,
 <xref rid="B11-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">11</xref>], and 
 <italic>H. longicollis</italic> (Welw.) Bolin [
 <xref rid="B5-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">5</xref>,
 <xref rid="B12-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">12</xref>]. Recently, two new 
 <italic>Hydnora</italic> species have been identified in different locations [
 <xref rid="B1-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">1</xref>,
 <xref rid="B5-plants-10-00494" ref-type="bibr">5</xref>].
</p>
